                       "message":  "SCENE-SAVE-WIRING: in-app Ctrl+S Save (Save-As, .rge-scene)\n\nWire in-app Save as the save-side mirror of SCENE-OPEN-WIRING (Ctrl+O),\ncalling the Dispatch-1 substrate rge_scene_loader::save_scene_world_to_path.\nSave-As only in v0: every Ctrl+S prompts for a destination; no\nscene_source_path / silent overwrite (a follow-up). editor-shell stays\ndependency-clean — the dialog + writer live behind two boxed-dyn traits; the\nbinary owns rfd + rge-scene-loader.\n\n- editor-shell: new lifecycle/save_request.rs with SceneSaveDialog\n  (pick_save_path) + SceneSaveHook (save_scene_world) traits and the public,\n  Editing-gated handle_save_request (dialog -\u003e writer -\u003e mark_saved only on\n  Ok; every failure path warn-logs + no-ops, is_dirty untouched).\n  with_scene_save_dialog / with_scene_save_hook builders + boxed-dyn fields\n  (preserved across replace_world). Ctrl+S already decodes to\n  EditorKeyCommand::MarkSaved; its handle_key_command arm is repointed from\n  mark_saved_command() to handle_save_request() (variant name retained; a\n  rename to Save is a deferred cosmetic follow-up).\n- rge-editor: binary-owned SceneSaveFileDialog (rfd save_file) +\n  SceneSaveWriterHook (derives Scene.name from the file stem, calls the\n  substrate), attached at all three launch sites.\n\n+7 headless editor-shell tests (writes-and-marks-saved, failure-doesn\u0027t-mark,\ncancel / no-dialog / no-hook / non-Editing no-ops, Ctrl+S routes to Save) and\n+1 binary SceneSaveWriterHook disk round-trip against the golden simple-scene.\nThe existing keyboard_command_bus_round_trip Ctrl+S test is updated to the new\nSave behavior (per the SCENE-SAVE-WIRING pre-exec correction round).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
