                       "message":  "SCENE-SAVE-WIRING: fix stale Ctrl+S comment (post-exec correction)\n\nRound-2 correction (post-exec review). The behavior change (Ctrl+S now\nroutes through Save and marks saved only after a successful write) made a\npre-existing comment in tests/inspector_snapshot_smoke.rs stale: it\nattributed the bare saved-point bookmark to Ctrl+S. The test body is\nunchanged (it calls mark_saved_command() directly); only the comment is\nrewritten to describe the direct mark-saved path plus the Ctrl+S/Save\ndistinction.\n\nAn unbounded stale-prose sweep (rg over the whole worktree) confirms this\nwas the sole stale reference; all other Ctrl+S prose is accurate. No\nruntime logic change.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
